  • Field Details

    • USE_EXISTING_CLAIM

      public static final ValueGenerator<Claim> USE_EXISTING_CLAIM
      Value generator that can be used with the ui ready exposure builders to force the builder to use the existing claim, rather than creating a new one. The pattern is to use: 
         ... claim builder ....
   .withExposure(ExposureBuilder.uiReadyXXXExposure(ExposureBuilder.USE_EXISTING_CLAIM)
   ... more claim builder calls ...
      This will cause the exposure builder to use the claim being built by the claim builder rather than creating a whole new claim

    • uiReadyBodilyInjuryDamage

      public static ExposureBuilder uiReadyBodilyInjuryDamage()
      Returns a builder that will create a new bodily injury damage exposure with its associated injury incident.

      If a claim is provided either explicitly via onClaim or implicitly, by calling this method as an argument to the ClaimBuilder withExposure method, then the specified claim will be used. Otherwise a new UI ready auto claim will be created. The exposure will be first party by default (use withLossParty to override). The exposure primary coverage and coverage subtype will be chosen to be compatible with the loss party type.

      The claimant and claimant type will be set according to the loss party type. For first party exposures the claimant will be set to the claim insured and the claimant type will be set to insured. For third party exposures the claimant will be set to a newly created person and the claimant type will be set to "other"

      The incident's injured party will be set to the exposure claimant, if possible, failing that the claim claimant or the insured. If all else fails a new person will be created as the injured party.

      Returns:
      a builder that can be used to create a bodily injury damage exposure on the given claim

    • uiReadyBodilyInjuryDamage

      public static ExposureBuilder uiReadyBodilyInjuryDamage(Claim claim)
      Returns a builder that will create a new first party, bodily injury damage exposure with its associated incident. The exposure claimant will be set to the claim insured unless the claim insured is a company, in which case it will be set to a newly created person. The exposure primary coverage and coverage subtype will be set to types that match the exposure type and are compatible with a first party loss type. The injury incident's injured party will be the exposure claimant.
      Parameters:
      claim - the claim on which to create the new exposure
      Returns:
      a builder that can be used to create a bodily injury damage exposure on the given claim
